Acknowledgements / Methodology Inspiration:

  No source code from the works in this section is imported into Y4.
  They are listed here separately from the reuse manifest above because
  Y4 owes them methodological inspiration (proof techniques, algorithmic
  patterns, demonstration of feasibility) without copying any code.

  * VeriSMo                "VeriSMo: A Verified Security Module for
                           Confidential VMs", Zhou et al.,
                           USENIX OSDI '24 (Best Paper Award).
                           https://www.usenix.org/conference/osdi24/presentation/zhou
                           Inspiration: 2-layer concurrency proof
                           pattern (paper §3-5). Y4 applies this with
                           layer inversion (cross-tenant upper / within-
                           cluster lower). See docs/vmm_arch.md §3.

  * Atmosphere             https://github.com/mars-research/atmosphere
                           SOSP '25 artifact, MIT-licensed Verus + Rust
                           microkernel work. Inspiration: demonstrates
                           that Verus is viable for OS-kernel-scale
                           verification. Y4 does not adopt Atmosphere's
                           AMD-V code (none is publicly published) but
                           uses the existence of Atmosphere as evidence
                           that the Verus + AMD-V combination is
                           tractable.

  * Linux cpufreq /        Algorithm reference only (no code import).
    cpuidle / thermal /    GPL-2-licensed; Apache-2 main tree cannot
    powercap drivers       import. Y4 power-mgr capsules study these
                           subsystems as reference for governor design,
                           thermal state machines, and RAPL exposure
                           patterns. Read-only refs at
                           ~/y4-upstream-refs/linux/. See
                           docs/power_arch.md §1.1.

  * Plundervolt            "Plundervolt: Software-based Fault Injection
    (USENIX Sec '20)       Attacks against Intel SGX", Murdock et al.
                           Mitigation reference for power_safety.md S23.4
                           (voltage range bound).

  * PLATYPUS               "PLATYPUS: Software-based Power Side-Channel
    (USENIX Sec '21)       Attacks on x86", Lipp et al. Mitigation
                           reference for power_safety.md S17 (RAPL
                           isolation).

  * Hertzbleed             "Hertzbleed: Turning Power Side-Channel Attacks
    (USENIX Sec '22)       Into Remote Timing Attacks on x86", Wang et al.
                           Mitigation reference for power_safety.md S15
                           (cpufreq isolation, DVFS dwell, constant-freq
                           mode).

